diffusionx provides CMake targets:

    find_package(diffusionx CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE diffusionx::diffusionx)

The library uses C++20 modules. Example usage:


    #include <print>
    import diffusionx.random;

    int main() {
        // Generate normal distribution samples
        auto normal = randn<double>(1000, 0.0, 1.0);
        if (normal) {
            std::println("Generated {} normal samples", normal->size());
        }
        
        // Generate uniform distribution samples  
        auto uniform = rand<double>(100, 0.0, 1.0);
        if (uniform) {
            std::println("Generated {} uniform samples", uniform->size());
        }
        return 0;
    }

Compiler requirements:
- C++23 standard support
- C++20 modules support
- LLVM/Clang 15.0+ (recommended)
- GCC 11.0+ (experimental)
- MSVC 19.29+ (Visual Studio 2022) 